I debugged that the reason the update is skipped, is because `previousSafeValue` will always be 0 when typing characters, so the assignment to `inputValue` always becomes 0=0.

However, then it seems that there is a lack of synchronization between the fact that the actual input value may be "0awaw", and the variable `inputValue` will be 0. Since the input `value` prop is 1-way binded to `inputValue` I would still expect them to be synchronized.

The above example can be resolved with something like: https://svelte.dev/repl/4afa6bc5639546d2a7026aceb5d4baa7?version=3.35.0


```javascript
<script lang="typescript">
  let bindedInputValue = 0;
  let previousBlockSize = 0;

  $: {
    if (!isNaN(+bindedInputValue)) {
      bindedInputValue = previousBlockSize = +bindedInputValue;
    } else {
      bindedInputValue = previousBlockSize;
    }
  }
</script>

 <input bind:value={bindedInputValue} />
```

