Setting the Svelte custom element props via setter only works when the custom element is defined, which is after the `./component.svelte` is loaded and executed.

Before that, `<my-component>` is a [HTMLUnknownElement](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLUnknownElement).

However, you can still set the attribute of `<my-component>` via [setAttribute()](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Element/setAttribute)

```js
const myComponent = document.createElement('my-component');
myComponent.setAttribute('name', 'Hello World');
document.body.appendChild(myComponent);
```

To know when the custom element is loaded and executed, you can `await` for the lazy import to be finished

```js
await import('my-component.js'); // at some point later

myComponent.name = 'Hello World again';
```

