As a workaround for now: If you would like to "disable" intro for a specific component and can afford to use `tick` instead of `css`, you could do something like this:
https://codesandbox.io/s/busy-sara-2fds6?file=/App.svelte
```javascript
  let localIntro = false;
  let introDone = false;

  const tick = node => {
    return {
      duration: 500,
      tick: p => {
        if (p === 1 && !introDone) {
          introDone = true;
          return;
        } else if (introDone === false && !localIntro) {
          return;
        }

        node.style.width = p * clientWidth + "px";
        node.style.height = p * clientHeight + "px";
      }
    };
  };
```

