Example
```ts
function update() {
	let i = 0;
	let v;
	for (v of el_tr) arr[i++] = v;
	arr.length = i;
}
```

Compiled
```ts
function update() {
	let i = 0;
	let v;
	for (v of el_tr) $$invalidate(1, arr[i++] = v, arr);
	$$invalidate(1, arr.length = i, arr);
}
```

Svelte's reactivity system involves calling `$$invalidate` on every local var reassignment
injecting likely superfluous function calls in situations such as in for loops without raising user's awareness should be a huge concern

I suggest adding an alternate component init function in dev mode whereby each superfluous `$$invalidate` call per update cycle is counted and reset `after_update` so as to warn the user when certain variables are invalidated hundreds of times in the span of a single tick

